@startuml 06-bandwidth-enforcement

!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
title Flow 6: Bandwidth Quota Enforcement

actor "End User" as User
participant "Platform\nBackend" as Backend
participant "Platform\nSmart Contract" as Contract
database "Sui\nBlockchain" as Sui

== Normal Request Flow ==

User -> Backend: GET /v/{video_id}/stream.m3u8

Backend -> Backend: Lookup video -> dev_account

Backend -> Contract: get_bandwidth_status(dev_account)
Contract -> Sui: Read DeveloperAccount
Sui --> Contract: {\n  bandwidth_quota: 1000 GB,\n  bandwidth_used: 950 GB\n}
Contract --> Backend: quota_remaining: 50 GB

alt quota_remaining > 0
    Backend -> Backend: Serve video normally
    Backend --> User: Video content
else quota_remaining <= 0
    Backend --> User: 429 Too Many Requests\n{\n  error: "bandwidth_exceeded",\n  message: "Video owner's quota exceeded",\n  retry_after: null\n}

    note right of Backend
      Developer must deposit more SUI
      to restore bandwidth quota.

      All their videos become
      unviewable until topped up.
    end note
end

== Developer Tops Up ==

actor "Developer" as Dev

Dev -> Contract: deposit(amount: 50 SUI)
Contract -> Sui: Update DeveloperAccount {\n  balance += 50 SUI,\n  bandwidth_quota += 500 GB\n}
Sui --> Contract: Success
Contract --> Dev: Bandwidth restored\nNew quota: 1500 GB

note right of Dev
  Videos immediately become
  viewable again after deposit.
end note

@enduml
